eltMesL2TunnelConfig.name: eltMesL2TunnelConfig

revisions.description: Deprecate all objects in this module.

eltMesL2TunnelConfig.description: This MIB module is for layer 2 tunneling related configurations on a device. Tunneling allows separate local networks to be considered as a single VLAN. These separate networks are connected via an ISP, which will tunnel the packets from one network to another, making it appear as if the two networks are actually just one.

EltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex.name: EltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex
EltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex.description: A tunneled protocol of an interface. Supported value is stp(1).

eltLtcNotificationEnable.name: eltLtcNotificationEnable
eltLtcNotificationEnable.description: This object indicates whether the system will generate the eltLtcTunnelDropThresholdExceeded and eltLtcTunnelShutdownThresholdExceeded notifications.

eltLtcTunnelMacAddress.name: eltLtcTunnelMacAddress
eltLtcTunnelMacAddress.description: The destination MAC address that replaces the original destination MAC address of tunneled frames.

eltLtcTunneledProtocolTable.name: eltLtcTunneledProtocolTable
eltLtcTunneledProtocolTable.description: This table contains information about the protocols being tunneled. Only tunneled protocol filtering capable interfaces are shown.

eltLtcTunneledProtocolEntry.name: eltLtcTunneledProtocolEntry
eltLtcTunneledProtocolEntry.description: Information about the protocols being tunneled. Only tunneled protocol filtering capable interfaces are shown.

eltLtcTunneledProtocolType.name: eltLtcTunneledProtocolType
eltLtcTunneledProtocolType.description: Indicates tunneled protocol of the interface. If a BIT is set, then the value of the corresponding protocol is tunneled. Specifically, if the 'stp(0)' BIT is set, then the Spanning Tree Protocol PDU is tunneled. At this moment, there are no other supported protocols. If the bit for a given protocol is set for an interface, then the statistics for that interface and protocol will start to be monitored.

eltLtcTunnelCos.name: eltLtcTunnelCos
eltLtcTunnelCos.description: Specifies the user priority of the tunneled PDUs for the interface.

eltLtcTunnelThresholdTable.name: eltLtcTunnelThresholdTable
eltLtcTunnelThresholdTable.description: This table contains information about the thresholds for protocol tunneling. Only tunneled protocol filtering capable interfaces are shown. The objects will be on a per interface, per protocol basis.

eltLtcTunnelThresholdEntry.name: eltLtcTunnelThresholdEntry
eltLtcTunnelThresholdEntry.description: Information about the thresholds for protocol tunneling. Only tunneled protocol filtering capable interfaces are shown. The entries will be on a per interface, per protocol basis

eltLtcTunnelThresholdProtocolIndex.name: eltLtcTunnelThresholdProtocolIndex
eltLtcTunnelThresholdProtocolIndex.description: A tunneled protocol of an interface.

eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold.name: eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold
eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold.description: The drop threshold on an interface for a given protocol. After reaching this drop threshold, the interface will start dropping PDUs for the given protocol. This value cannot be greater than the value of eltLtcTunnelShutdownThreshold. A value of 0 indicates that no limit is set.

eltLtcTunnelShutdownThreshold.name: eltLtcTunnelShutdownThreshold
eltLtcTunnelShutdownThreshold.description: The shutdown threshold on an interface for a given protocol. After reaching the shutdown threshold, the interface will shutdown for the given protocol. This value cannot be less than the value of eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold. A value of 0 indicates that no limit is set.

eltLtcTunnelStatisticsTable.name: eltLtcTunnelStatisticsTable
eltLtcTunnelStatisticsTable.description: This table contains protocol tunneling statistics on the interface.

eltLtcTunnelStatisticsEntry.name: eltLtcTunnelStatisticsEntry
eltLtcTunnelStatisticsEntry.description: Protocol tunneling statistics on the interface.

eltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex.name: eltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex
eltLtcTunneledProtocolIndex.description: A tunneled protocol of an interface.

eltLtcTunnelEncapStats.name: eltLtcTunnelEncapStats
eltLtcTunnelEncapStats.description: The tunneled PDU encapsulation statistics of an interface. These statistics cover the number of tunneled ingress PDUs.

eltLtcTunnelDecapStats.name: eltLtcTunnelDecapStats
eltLtcTunnelDecapStats.description: The tunneled PDU de-encapsulation statistics of an interface. These statistics cover the number of tunneled egress PDUs.

eltLtcTunnelDropStats.name: eltLtcTunnelDropStats
eltLtcTunnelDropStats.description: The number of PDUs dropped on an interface for a given protocol. The PDUs will be dropped when the eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold is reached.

eltLtcTunnelDropThresholdExceeded.name: eltLtcTunnelDropThresholdExceeded
eltLtcTunnelDropThresholdExceeded.description: This notification is generated when the eltLtcTunnelDropThreshold has been exceeded.

eltLtcTunnelShutdownThresholdExceeded.name: eltLtcTunnelShutdownThresholdExceeded
eltLtcTunnelShutdownThresholdExceeded.description: This notification is generated when the eltLtcTunnelShutdownThreshold has been exceeded.
